<plot>An external study of the internal struggle to define ones place in the everyday work world. Two men stand at odds in a small office separated by two shafts of color. Each day is an exhaustive exercise in vice as the the man in red surrenders to his primal sensibilities and must confront his need to destroy the man sitting across the room. Is it choice? Is it fatalism? It is internal desire to suspend ones self from the constructed world of high rises and facsimile machines, fearing no mortality and no repercussions.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?249501</url></doc>
